  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Stellaris Venture Partners India Trust II</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="2">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The Fund is focused on non-manufacturing early stage technology startups in India. Activities to be supported by this investment are expected to have minimal or no adverse environmental or social impacts. Hence, the project is categorized as Category FI-3 in accordance with IFC&apos;s Environmental and Social Sustainability Policy. The project will not support coal related or higher risk activities. This is an existing client with an existing E&amp;S risk management system (ESMS) and E&amp;S officer responsible for implementation. The current ESMS will be required to be applied for this project as well. Applicable requirements will include IFC Exclusion List and relevant national E&amp;S laws and regulations if they exist and are applicable.</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The proposed project is an equity investment of up to US$25 million in Stellaris Venture Partners India Trust II (Fund), a trust domiciled in India. The Fund focuses primarily on seed and series A investments in Indian technology-enabled companies and is targeting US$160 million in total commitments. The Fund plans to invest in 20-25 companies across healthcare, education, financial services, logistics, consumer internet and enterprise technology sectors.</narrative>
  </description>
